  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Maximum sentences can increase for more complex or larger-scale laundering\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved\n- Potential forfeitures of assets connected to laundered funds\n\n3. Additional consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Asset seizure\n\nSpecific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, intent, and prior criminal history. Prosecution typically occurs through federal agencies like the Department of Justice.",
